{{Quote|Reprensentatives&mdash;please! This is ''wrong.'' We are the ''Convocation.'' We stand for peace. For ''unity.''<nowiki />|Representative Kilan T'Dara, to other reprensentatives who were attempting to attack an envoy of the Yacombe|<ref name="Peace and Unity">{{StoryCite|story=Peace and Unity|book=The High Republic (2022) 1}}</ref>}}
The '''Convocation of the Force''', also known more simply as the '''Convocation'''<ref name="Peace and Unity" /> or the '''Force Convocation''',<ref name="Battle of Jedha script">[[The High Republic: The Battle of Jedha (script)|''The High Republic: The Battle of Jedha'' script]]</ref> was an [[advisor]]y body and council designed to promote understanding between the various [[The Force|Force]] [[religion]]s based on the [[desert]]<ref name="Peace and Unity" /> [[moon]]<ref name="POD" /> [[Jedha]] during the [[High Republic Era]].<ref name="Peace and Unity" /> Formed a few years before [[382 BBY]]<ref name="Formation Date" /> religions with [[representative]]s on the Convocation included the [[Disciples of the Whills]], the [[Fallanassi]], the [[Lonto]], the [[Matukai]],<ref name="Peace and Unity" /> the [[Jedi Order]], the [[Guardians of the Whills]], the [[Church of the Force]], and the [[Sorcerers of Tund]].<ref name="POD" /> Shortly into its existence,<ref name="Bad Customer">{{InsiderCite|issue1=217|issue2=218|Tales of Enlightenment: No Such Thing as a Bad Customer}}</ref> the Convocation was [[Chairman|chaired]] by Representative [[Kilan T'Dara]] of the Church of the Force.<ref name="THR 4">[[The High Republic (2022) 4|''The High Republic'' (2022) 4]]</ref> At that time, the [[Path of the Open Hand]] cult, a small religion based on the planet [[Dalna]], had no presence on Jedha, but the [[Evereni]] follower [[Marda Ro]] wished to spread their word to the moon and join the Convocation as the Path's representative when [[Padawan]] [[Kevmo Zink]] suggested as such. Although the cult's leader, [[Elecia Zeveron]], disapproved of the idea, former leader<ref name="POD" /> [[Werth Plouth]]<ref name="THR 4" /> was intrigued and supportive of spreading to Jedha.<ref name="POD" />

In 382 [['ABY-BBY' dating system|BBY]],<ref name="Date">''[[Star Wars: The High Republic Character Encyclopedia]]'' dates the events of [[The High Republic (2022) 1|''The High Republic'' (2022) 1]] to [[382 BBY]].</ref> the Convocation planned to hold a festival known as the [[Festival of Balance]]<ref name="The High Republic 1">[[The High Republic (2022) 1|''The High Republic'' (2022) 1]]</ref> in [[Jedha City]], which was projected to bring in large amounts of tourists. The dock worker [[Piralli]] commented on the festival to [[adjunct]] [[Keth Cerepath]] during a particularly busy night at the [[Cantina|tapbar]] [[Enlightenment]], which both were regulars of. However,<ref name="New Prospects" /> [[Kradon Minst]],<ref name="The High Republic 2">[[The High Republic (2022) 2|''The High Republic'' (2022) 2]]</ref> the bar's owner, thought that the festival would be good for business.<ref name="New Prospects" /> In the same [[Standard year|year]],<ref name="Date" /> the [[Yacombe]] applied for membership on the council but ultimately retracted their offer after a number of the current representatives attempted to attack the [[Yacombe Delegate|Yacombe envoy]] sent.<ref name="Peace and Unity" />

Over a month later after the Path left Dalna,<ref name="Battle of Jedha">''[[The High Republic: The Battle of Jedha]]''</ref> Plouth, accompanied by [[Yana Ro]] and [[Radicaz Dobbs]], adressed the Convocation, demanding the council to be dissolved.<ref name="THR 4" /> After Leebon's [[death]] during the [[Battle of Jedha]], her [[aide]] [[Oliviah Zeveron]] was expected to succeed her, but due to injuries Zeveron sustained during the battle she was advised to return to [[Coruscant]] to recover and Jedi [[Vildar Mac]] took her place on the Convocation. The former Guardian of the Whills [[Tey Sirrek]] was also given a seat on the council to represent those who did not belong to any of the major Force factions.<ref name="Path of Vengeance">''[[The High Republic: Path of Vengeance]]''</ref>

